Sithembile Ncwane,23, was returned home after she was kidnapped last Friday. Ncwane was allegedly dropped home by her kidnappers on Saturday, with a few injuries and was taken to hospital for medical checks. It is alleged that the victim was walking along Khululeka Drive, when she texted her mother that there was a suspicious vehicle that was following her. When the mother phoned back, her cellphone was already off. The mother then contacted the police prompting a search. Provincial police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele said a case of kidnapping has been opened and Kwadabeka SAPS are investigating further.